<subSubSection pageId="40" pageNumber="191" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1437,151,501]" pageId="40" pageNumber="191">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,188,213]" pageId="40" pageNumber="191">Remarks</emphasis>
. Only likely to be confused with 
<taxonomicName box="[680,795,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Ptiliidae" genus="Acrotrichis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="191" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minuscula">
<emphasis box="[680,795,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="191">minuscula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[849,924,189,212]" class="Insecta" family="Ptiliidae" genus="Acrotrichis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="191" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exigua">
<emphasis box="[849,924,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="191">exigua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Compared to the former the pronotum is less curved, the aedeagus is shorter and the spines on ventrite six more closely packed together. In addition the spermatheca is quite different, it is however very similar to that of 
<taxonomicName box="[927,1042,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Ptiliidae" genus="Acrotrichis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="191" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minuscula">
<emphasis box="[927,1042,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="191">minuscula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but it may be separated from that species by the form of the pronotum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
